document_title: Corneal ulcers: Causes, symptoms and prevention
subsection_content:
A corneal ulcer is an eye infection that causes open sores on the cornea. Symptoms and complications vary depending on the disease and the causative agent.
Slight contact from dust, soil, rubbing eyes... is the cause of corneal ulcers
